{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2022,"text":"This back here was my brain cancer."},{"time":7125,"text":"Isn't it nice?"},{"time":8869,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":11336,"text":"The key phrase is \"was,\""},{"time":13822,"text":"phew."},{"time":15481,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20547,"text":"Having brain cancer was really,\nas you can imagine,"},{"time":24739,"text":"shocking news for me."},{"time":26615,"text":"I knew nothing about cancer."},{"time":30059,"text":"In Western cultures, when you have cancer,"},{"time":33894,"text":"it's as if you disappear in a way."},{"time":36509,"text":"Your life as a complex human being\nis replaced by medical data:"},{"time":43147,"text":"Your images, your exams, your lab values,"},{"time":49258,"text":"a list of medicines."},{"time":51740,"text":"And everyone changes as well."},{"time":54439,"text":"You suddenly become a disease on legs."},{"time":57384,"text":"Doctors start speaking a language\nwhich you don't understand."},{"time":61983,"text":"They start pointing their fingers"},{"time":67337,"text":"at your body and your images."},{"time":72187,"text":"People start changing as well"},{"time":75234,"text":"because they start dealing\nwith the disease,"},{"time":79100,"text":"instead of with the human being."},{"time":81459,"text":"They say, \"What did the doctor say?\""},{"time":83644,"text":"before even saying, \"Hello.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87976,"text":"And in the meanwhile,"},{"time":89923,"text":"you're left with questions\nto which nobody gives an answer."},{"time":95113,"text":"These are the \"Can I?\" questions:"},{"time":97888,"text":"Can I work while I have cancer?"},{"time":100507,"text":"Can I study? Can I make love?\nCan I be creative?"},{"time":105864,"text":"And you wonder, \"What have I done\nto deserve this?\""},{"time":109342,"text":"You wonder, \"Can I change something\nabout my lifestyle?\""},{"time":113500,"text":"You wonder, \"Can I do something?"},{"time":116198,"text":"Are there any other options?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":120333,"text":"And, obviously, doctors are\nthe good guys in all these scenarios,"},{"time":125988,"text":"because they are very professional\nand dedicated to curing you."},{"time":131934,"text":"But they also are very used\nto having to deal with patients,"},{"time":137192,"text":"so I'd say that they sometimes\nlose the idea that this is torture for you"},{"time":144148,"text":"and that you become,\nliterally, a patient --"},{"time":149103,"text":"\"patient\" means \"the one who waits.\""},{"time":151538,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":152955,"text":"Things are changing, but classically,"},{"time":157168,"text":"they tend to not engage you in any way\nto learn about your condition,"},{"time":162841,"text":"to get your friends and family engaged,"},{"time":166988,"text":"or showing you ways\nin which you can change your lifestyle"},{"time":170752,"text":"to minimize the risks\nof what you're going through."},{"time":174083,"text":"But instead, you're forced there to wait"},{"time":177971,"text":"in the hands of a series\nof very professional strangers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184815,"text":"While I was in the hospital,"},{"time":186914,"text":"I asked for a printed-out\npicture of my cancer"},{"time":190356,"text":"and I spoke with it."},{"time":193120,"text":"It was really hard to obtain,"},{"time":195342,"text":"because it's not common practice\nto ask for a picture of your own cancer."},{"time":200294,"text":"I talked to it and I said,"},{"time":202083,"text":"\"Okay, cancer,\nyou're not all there is to me."},{"time":206635,"text":"There's more to me."},{"time":208647,"text":"A cure, whichever it is, will have\nto deal with the whole of me.\""},{"time":215086,"text":"And so, the next day, I left the hospital\nagainst medical advice."},{"time":221024,"text":"I was determined to change\nmy relationship with the cancer"},{"time":225616,"text":"and I was determined\nto learn more about my cancer"},{"time":228484,"text":"before doing anything\nas drastic as a surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234037,"text":"I'm an artist, I use several forms\nof open-source technologies"},{"time":240951,"text":"and open information in my practice."},{"time":243494,"text":"So my best bet was to get it all\nout there, get the information out there,"},{"time":249605,"text":"and use it so that it could be\naccessed by anyone."},{"time":256269,"text":"So I created a website,\nwhich is called La Cura,"},{"time":260246,"text":"on which I put my medical data, online."},{"time":263398,"text":"I actually had to hack it"},{"time":265295,"text":"and that's a thing which we\ncan talk about in another speech."},{"time":269475,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":270822,"text":"I chose this word, La Cura --"},{"time":273403,"text":"La Cura in Italian means \"the cure\" --"},{"time":275762,"text":"because in many different cultures,"},{"time":278514,"text":"the word \"cure\" can mean\nmany different things."},{"time":283066,"text":"In our Western cultures,"},{"time":284749,"text":"it means eradicating\nor reversing a disease,"},{"time":289242,"text":"but in different cultures,"},{"time":290770,"text":"for example, a culture from Asia,"},{"time":294350,"text":"from the Mediterranean,\nfrom Latin countries, from Africa,"},{"time":298486,"text":"it can mean many more things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300628,"text":"Of course, I was interested\nin the opinions of doctors"},{"time":306015,"text":"and healthcare providers,"},{"time":308264,"text":"but I was also interested in\nthe cure of the artist, of the poet,"},{"time":314259,"text":"of the designer,"},{"time":316436,"text":"of, who knows, the musicians."},{"time":320889,"text":"I was interested in the social cure,"},{"time":323789,"text":"I was interested in\nthe psychological cure,"},{"time":326487,"text":"I was interested in the spiritual cure,"},{"time":329001,"text":"I was interested in the emotional cure,"},{"time":332059,"text":"I was interested in any form of cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336920,"text":"And, it worked."},{"time":340616,"text":"The La Cura website went viral."},{"time":343969,"text":"I received lots of media attention\nfrom Italy and from abroad"},{"time":348694,"text":"and I quickly received\nmore than 500,000 contacts --"},{"time":354440,"text":"emails, social networking --"},{"time":356378,"text":"most of them were a suggestion\non how to cure my cancer,"},{"time":359573,"text":"but more of them were about\nhow to cure myself"},{"time":363004,"text":"as a full individual."},{"time":366283,"text":"For example, many thousands of videos,"},{"time":370365,"text":"images, pictures, art performances"},{"time":374319,"text":"were produced for La Cura."},{"time":376756,"text":"For example, here we see\nFrancesca Fini in her performance."},{"time":381141,"text":"Or, as artist Patrick Lichty has done:"},{"time":385522,"text":"He produced a 3D sculpture of my tumor"},{"time":390100,"text":"and put it on sale on Thingiverse."},{"time":392821,"text":"Now you can have my cancer, too!"},{"time":395044,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":397581,"text":"Which is a nice thing,\nif you think about it,"},{"time":400998,"text":"we can share our cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404234,"text":"And this was going on --"},{"time":406633,"text":"scientists, the traditional\nmedicine experts,"},{"time":410018,"text":"several researchers, doctors --"},{"time":411705,"text":"all connected with me to give advice."},{"time":414401,"text":"With all this information and support,"},{"time":416320,"text":"I was able to form a team\nof several neurosurgeons,"},{"time":422009,"text":"traditional doctors,"},{"time":424995,"text":"oncologists, and several\nhundred volunteers"},{"time":431144,"text":"with whom I was able to discuss"},{"time":434373,"text":"the information I was receiving,\nwhich is very important."},{"time":439796,"text":"And together, we were able to form\na strategy for my own cure"},{"time":446165,"text":"in many languages,\naccording to many cultures."},{"time":449816,"text":"And the current strategy\nspans the whole world"},{"time":453005,"text":"and thousands of years of human history,"},{"time":455627,"text":"which is quite remarkable for me."},{"time":457710,"text":"[Surgery]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459394,"text":"The follow-up MRIs showed, luckily,\nlittle to no growth of the cancer."},{"time":465005,"text":"So I was able to take my time and choose."},{"time":468426,"text":"I chose the doctor I wanted to work with,"},{"time":472091,"text":"I chose the hospital I wanted to stay in,"},{"time":474489,"text":"and in the meanwhile, I was supported\nby thousands of people,"},{"time":478500,"text":"none of whom felt pity for me."},{"time":481751,"text":"Everyone felt like they could\ntake an active role"},{"time":487429,"text":"in helping me to get well,"},{"time":489265,"text":"and this was the most important\npart of La Cura."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494081,"text":"What are the outcomes?"},{"time":496122,"text":"I'm fine, as you can see, pretty fine."},{"time":498479,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":503795,"text":"I had excellent news"},{"time":506227,"text":"after the surgery --"},{"time":507857,"text":"I have -- I had a very low-grade glioma,"},{"time":513376,"text":"which is a \"good\" kind of cancer\nwhich doesn't grow a lot."},{"time":517822,"text":"I have completely changed\nmy life and my lifestyle."},{"time":522250,"text":"Everything I did was thoughtfully\ndesigned to get me engaged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528055,"text":"Up until the very last few\nminutes of the surgery,"},{"time":532195,"text":"which was very intense,"},{"time":534186,"text":"a matrix of electrodes\nwas implanted in my brain"},{"time":538131,"text":"from this side,"},{"time":540021,"text":"to be able to build a functional map\nof what the brain controls."},{"time":545278,"text":"And right before the operation,"},{"time":548976,"text":"we were able to discuss\nthe functional map of my brain"},{"time":555777,"text":"with the doctor, to understand\nwhich risks I was running into"},{"time":560684,"text":"and if there were any I wanted to avoid."},{"time":564312,"text":"Obviously, there were."},{"time":566452,"text":"[Open]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567529,"text":"And this openness was really\nthe fundamental part of La Cura."},{"time":572980,"text":"Thousands of people shared\ntheir stories, their experiences."},{"time":577799,"text":"Doctors got to talk with people\nthey don't usually consult"},{"time":582427,"text":"when they think about cancer."},{"time":587370,"text":"I'm a self-founding,\ncontinuous state of translation"},{"time":592043,"text":"among many different languages,"},{"time":594363,"text":"in which science meets emotion"},{"time":598260,"text":"and conventional research\nmeets traditional research."},{"time":602921,"text":"[Society]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":604263,"text":"The most important thing of La Cura"},{"time":609635,"text":"was to feel like a part\nof a really engaged and connected society"},{"time":616660,"text":"whose wellness really depends\non the wellness of all of its components."},{"time":624253,"text":"This global performance\nis my open-source cure for cancer."},{"time":629873,"text":"And from what I feel,"},{"time":631679,"text":"it's a cure for me, but for us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634079,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635256,"text":"(Applause)."}]}]}